{
  "texts": [
    "While the taxonomy of Liao et al. (2020) offers a general overview of question types, it falls short in connecting these questions to the distinct methods used for answering them.",
    "This gap becomes evident when realizing that a broad category, such as \"Why\" questions, can encompass diverse queries such as probing a specific classification or drawing comparisons between instances.",
    "To bridge this gap, Table 5 contrasts model-agnostic methods used to address these questions in various studies and shows which question they answer.",
    "As the table shows, \"Why\" questions are answered by different systems through local feature importance explanations, counterfactual explanations, or contrastive explanations.",
    "A notable trend we observed is the predominance of local feature importance explanations, which were employed in four of the five studies analyzed."
  ]
}